# Unity3D installation

# There is a linux version of Unity3D available since August, 2015!!!
# Just download the .deb file and run it: http://blogs.unity3d.com/2015/08/26/unity-comes-to-linux-experimental-build-now-available/


# It's better to install it through PlayOnLinux
# There's a good working guide here:
# http://wiki.unity3d.com/index.php/Running_Unity_on_Linux_through_Wine#Installation_with_PlayOnLinux

# Installation without PlayOnLinux (obsolete)
# wine and winetricks has to be installed
# NOT VERIFIED: Before doing anything, wine should be configured to work in 32 bit mode. Steps to make this:
# export WINEARCH=win32
# Move current ~/.wine directory somewhere
# The do all the following steps. And only after all steps will be implemented, run unity
# VERIFIED:
winetricks tahoma
winetricks d3dx9
winetricks dotnet20
winetricks dotnet40 - may not be necessary
winetricks corefonts
winetricks forcemono

mkdir -p ~/.wine/drive_c/users/mikhail/AppData/LocalLow


